          "date": "2011-03-17 21:02:52.000000000",
          "tz": 60
        },
        "subject": "LU-114 use ll_lookup_one_len() instead of lookup_one_len() in sptlrpc_target_local_copy_conf() should lock the parent dir when doing lookup",
        "message": "LU-114 use ll_lookup_one_len() instead of lookup_one_len() in sptlrpc_target_local_copy_conf() should lock the parent dir when doing lookup\n\nRecent kernels print a warning when lookup_one_len() is called w/o the parent dir locked.\nsptlrpc_target_local_copy_conf() should not call lookup_one_len() directly, but ll_lookup_one_len()\ninstead which locks the parent dir for you and also checks for bad inode.\n\nChange-Id: I4d020c55382238bbbc6df6017f54b5b585f53c48\nSigned-off-by: Johann Lombardi <johann@whamcloud.com>\n"
      },
      "branch": "refs/heads/master"
    }
  },
